## 6. SIMPLIFIED TEXTUAL UML REPRESENTATION

```
Actor: Administrator

Administrator → Admin Login
Administrator → Access Admin Dashboard

[User & Account Management]
Administrator → View Client Accounts
Administrator → Manage Client Records
Administrator → Manage Staff Accounts
    «include» Create Staff Account
    «include» Update Staff Account
    «include» Disable Staff Account

[Service & Package Management]
Administrator → Manage Funeral Packages
    «include» Create Funeral Package
    «include» Update Funeral Package
    «include» Remove Funeral Package
Administrator → Manage Chapel Services
    «include» Add Chapel Service
    «include» Update Chapel Availability
Administrator → Update Service Pricing

[Booking Management]
Administrator → View All Bookings
Administrator → Review Booking Requests
    «include» Approve Booking
    «include» Reject Booking
Administrator → Manage Service Schedules
    «include» Assign Schedule
    «include» Modify Schedule
Administrator → Update Service Status
Administrator → Monitor Service Progress

[Document Management]
Administrator → View All Client Documents
Administrator → Review Uploaded Documents
Administrator → Approve Documents
Administrator → Reject Documents
    «extend» Archive Documents

[Financial Control]
Administrator → Generate Billing Statement
    «include» Create Invoice
    «include» Generate Digital Receipt
Administrator → Monitor Online Payments
Administrator → Monitor Donations
Administrator → View Transaction History

[Reports & Analytics]
Administrator → Generate Financial Reports
Administrator → Generate Operational Reports
Administrator → Generate Client Reports
Administrator → View Reports
    «extend» Export Reports

[Content Management]
Administrator → Manage Announcements
    «include» Create Announcement
    «include» Update Announcement
    «include» Remove Announcement
Administrator → Manage Obituaries
    «include» Create Obituary
    «include» Update Obituary
    «include» Remove Obituary

[System Oversight]
Administrator → Monitor System Operations
Administrator → View System Activity Logs
Administrator → Ensure Data Integrity

Administrator → Admin Logout
```

